  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1  \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Check in at the police station to get fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister Kanchana Wijesekera has requested the tricycle drivers to register at the police station in their area and reserve a filling station for getting fuel.",
        "In addition, he said today (26) by posting a message on Twitter to make a reply before the upcoming 31st.",
        "He also mentioned that from the first day of August, fuel for tricycles can be obtained only from fuel filling stations registered with the police station.",
        "He also said that those who use agricultural equipment, generators and other equipment can register in their respective divisional secretariats.",
        "They can register with weekly fuel requirement information and reserve any fuel station in the area.",
        "Meanwhile, the Minister has mentioned that those who cannot register through the QR system through the basic code known as Chesi, can register using the vehicle income tax permit from Friday."
      ],
